Still on covid-19, the surge of covid 19 numbers during the third wave is causing alarm bells. since the year began, a positivity rate of above 10% has been recorded in the country, an indication that the situation could worsen if Kenyans fail to strictly adhere to the containment measures. In the last 24 hours alone, 870 new covid 19 infections were recorded while 7 patients died. and as our health and science reporter Beldeen Waliaula reports, there is concern that the country may not be getting the exact picture of the covid 19 situation because of the low number of tests being done